The paper deals with combinatorial properties of words, specifically the number of distinct squares in a word. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of combinatorics and optimization, which could fall under the categories of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The construction of words with high distinct-square-densities involves analyzing the properties of the words, which could fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
